inputs.name: Args
inputs.description: A string. Additional parameters to the command.

inputs.name: Coord mm
inputs.description: A boolean. All coordinates in mm.

inputs.name: Coord vox
inputs.description: A boolean. All coordinates in voxels - default.

inputs.name: Environ
inputs.description: A dictionary with keys which are a value of type 'str' and with values which are a value of type 'str'. Environment variables.

inputs.name: Ignore exception
inputs.description: A boolean. Print an error message instead of throwing an exception in case the interface fails to run.

inputs.name: Img file
inputs.description: An existing file name. Filename of input image.

inputs.name: In coords
inputs.description: An existing file name. Filename of file containing coordinates.

inputs.name: Out file
inputs.description: A file name. Output file name.

inputs.name: Premat file
inputs.description: An existing file name. Filename of pre-warp affine transform (e.g. example_func2highres.mat).

inputs.name: Std file
inputs.description: An existing file name. Filename of destination image.

inputs.name: Terminal output
inputs.description: 'stream' or 'allatonce' or 'file' or 'none'. Control terminal output: `stream` - displays to terminal immediately (default), `allatonce` - waits till command is finished to display output, `file` - writes output to file, `none` - output is ignored.

inputs.name: Warp file
inputs.description: An existing file name. Filename of warpfield (e.g. intermediate2dest_warp.nii.gz).

inputs.name: Xfm file
inputs.description: An existing file name. Filename of affine transform (e.g. source2dest.mat).

name: WarpPointsToStd
description: WarpPointsToStd, as implemented in Nipype (module: nipype.interfaces.fsl, interface: WarpPointsToStd).
